thread.title: Leonard's late TD's sink Spanish River
thread.title_full: Leonard's late TD's sink Spanish River - Sun Sentinel

author: Rick Menning
title: Leonard's late TD's sink Spanish River
text:
John I. Leonard struck for three big-play touchdowns in the second half to upset host Spanish River, 28-14, in a District 10-8A match-up.
With the score tied at 14-14, Vitaldo David put the Lancers ahead early in the fourth quarter when he picked up a loose ball on the Sharks' 40 and had a clear field to the end zone.
On Leonard's next possession, Jeremiah Blatch capped a four-play, 60-yard drive when he scampered around the left side for a 30-yard touchdown with five minutes remaining.
The Lancers (2-4, 2-1) erased a 14-6 halftime deficit with another long touchdown as Anthony Wynds Jr. burst up the middle for 30 yards to set the stage for the decisive final quarter.
The Sharks (4-3, 1-3) capitalized on a Jancers' turnover seven seconds before halftime,with Dimitrius Hirsch intercepting a pass and returning it 80 yards down the right sideline.
Leonard had put the first six points on the scoreboard just minutes into the second quarter when Kailen King cut right and scored from 15 yards out.
